tical light curve\nalone. We find significant echo signals, consistent with the optical lags found\nusing the discrete cross-correlation. We speculate that whilst some of the\ndriving X-ray emission is reflected by the disk, some is absorbed and\nre-processed on the thermal timescale, giving rise to both the observed optical\nlags and optical echoes.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 28 May 2015 20:00:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-07-15"}
